 {"id": "franken_networkx-stalexf", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] stale pytest.xfail for codtrav hid the (now-fixed) topological_sort parity", "description": "test_cod_conformance_matrix.test_traversal_matches_networkx_matrix unconditionally called pytest.xfail for the topological_sort case, hiding the real test. codtrav-review was closed by the Python-level Kahn's algorithm wrapper (br-zzcm7 sibling fix). Removed the stale xfail so the matrix actually exercises topological_sort now.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:39:08.821868Z", "close_reason": "Removed pytest.xfail; the DAG topological_sort case now runs its real assertion (passes).", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:39:08.821868Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:39:08.821868Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-caveman", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] connected_caveman_graph does not remove within-clique edge; 3 extras per (l, k)", "description": "fnx.connected_caveman_graph adds the bridge edge to the next clique but never removed the within-clique edge, so the output has l extra edges beyond nx's output. nx's ref impl: `G.remove_edge(start, start+1); G.add_edge(start, (start-1) % (l*k))`. Fix replicates the rewiring exactly, including the k<2 ValueError.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:46:12.304582Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:46:12.304582Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:46:12.304582Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in round 11 cycle 2."}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-navsw", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] navigable_small_world_graph uses bounding-box instead of Manhattan distance", "description": "fnx's Python implementation of navigable_small_world_graph iterated a (2p+1)^dim bounding box for local edges without filtering by Manhattan distance, massively overcounting local edges (72 vs 31 on n=3, p=1). nx uses `d = sum(abs(b-a)...); if d <= p`. Long-range picks also used a different RNG CDF pattern. Rewrote to match nx exactly including accumulate + bisect_left CDF sampling.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:46:12.304582Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:46:12.304582Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:46:12.304582Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in round 11 cycle 2."}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-mgedgeeq", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] MultiGraph.edges(keys=True) == {...} returns False (list-vs-set mismatch)", "description": "nx's MultiEdgeView inherits from Set, so `MG.edges(keys=True) == {(0,1,0),(0,1,1),(1,2,0)}` returns True. fnx returns an `_EdgeListWithSetAlgebra` list subclass; list.__eq__ only supports list-to-list so the same comparison returned False. Added __eq__/__ne__ on _EdgeListWithSetAlgebra that compares as set when RHS is set/frozenset; falls back to list.__eq__ otherwise. Also set __hash__ = None per Python protocol.", "status": "closed", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T08:51:28.310322Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: _EdgeListWithSetAlgebra now compares as set against set/frozenset RHS.", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T08:51:28.310322Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T08:51:28.310322Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
